  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are caught in negative gamma territory with SPX at 6517.32, sitting right between the massive -8.3B gamma pit at 6500 and positive gamma resistance at 6515—expect choppy, volatile action as dealers flip between buying dips toward 6500 and selling rallies above 6515. The breakout regime with -314M total GEX means any sustained move will be amplified by dealer hedging, particularly dangerous if we break below 6500 where dealers will aggressively buy the dip, or if we clear the 6515-6535 resistance zone where selling pressure kicks in. Watch 6500 as the critical support—break below triggers dealer buying but also opens the door to the next major gamma pit at 6400 (-4.2B), while any push above 6535 faces diminishing positive gamma support toward the 6840 flip level.",
